        "title": "Site Selection",
        "file": "Site-Selection.html",
        "headings": [],
        "body": "A vendor admin account is granted access to all connected states by default. To provide EHR integrations for a state, at least one SRS is required for that state. This means that a vendor admin will need to set up a new SRS for each state they provide integrations for. The following subsection details how you can switch between different sites (PDMPs). In the top right corner of the RxConsole Screen, you will see the Site Code(s) Selector. In the top right corner of the RxConsole Screen, you will see the Site Code(s) Selector. In the top right corner of the RxConsole Screen, you will see the Site Code(s) Selector. Press the blue dropdown to open a new window that allows you to select a new site. Press the blue dropdown to open a new window that allows you to select a new site. Press the blue dropdown to open a new window that allows you to select a new site. You will see the following window display titled Change Site . You will see the following window display titled Change Site . You will see the following window display titled Change Site . By clicking on the desired tab, you can search for the PDMP, HCE, or GROUPs you have access to. By clicking on the desired tab, you can search for the PDMP, HCE, or GROUPs you have access to. By clicking on the desired tab, you can search for the PDMP, HCE, or GROUPs you have access to. To navigate to a desired site, press the Select Site button. To navigate to a desired site, press the Select Site button. To navigate to a desired site, press the Select Site button. Verify that your site has changed by viewing the two-letter code in the blue dropdown box in the top right corner of the RxConsole. Verify that your site has changed by viewing the two-letter code in the blue dropdown box in the top right corner of the RxConsole. Verify that your site has changed by viewing the two-letter code in the blue dropdown box in the top right corner of the RxConsole. Note: If you are unable to find a HCE or GROUP you believe you should have access to, you may need to verify that the site was assigned to you by the PDMP administrator for the respective state."
